Forty-Nine People Injured in Uganda Inflation Protests, New Vision Reports

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-04-15T05:19:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/forty-nine-people-injured-in-uganda-inflation-protests-new-vision-reports.html
At least 49 people were injured
yesterday, including Kizza Besigye, the leader of the opposition
Forum for Democratic Change, who was shot in the hand, as Uganda
police and military blocked processions against rising
inflation, New Vision reported, citing Uganda Red Cross.  The people were injured during clashes with the police and
military who blocked the “walk-to-work” protests, the Kampala-
based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  